---
import SectionHeading from "~/components/ui/SectionHeading.astro";
import Tag from "~/components/ui/Tag.astro";

const competencies = [
  "Power Electronics",
  "Sonar & Acoustics",
  "Undersea Systems & Autonomy",
  "Directed Energy / HEL",
  "Systems Engineering",
  "Hardware Lifecycle",
  "R&D Leadership",
  "Technical Leadership",
  "System Architecture",
  "Team Management",
  "Program Execution",
];
---

<section id="about" aria-labelledby="about-heading" class="scroll-mt-24">
  <SectionHeading title="About" />

  <div class="space-y-5 text-slate">
    <p>
      My work sits at the intersection of undersea systems, sonar, autonomy,
      power electronics, and system integration. I currently lead the Power
      Electronics and System Design group at General Atomics Electromagnetic
      Systems in San Diego, supporting high-energy laser and electro-optical
      programs for U.S. defense customers. Previously, I served as Chief
      Engineer and Senior Manager at L3Harris, leading the manufacturing and
      delivery of Navy sonar systems including lightweight torpedo arrays,
      Virginia-class conformal arrays, airborne dipping sonar, and towed array
      systems.
    </p>

    <p>
      Before that, I led electrical development for autonomous underwater
      vehicles and subsea systems at Terradepth and Lockheed Martin, with work
      spanning subsea surveillance platforms, sonar suites, pressure-tolerant
      power systems, battery-powered architectures, and integrated maritime
      payloads.
    </p>

    <p>
      Today, I advise startups, small businesses, and engineering teams that
      need senior technical judgment on hard hardware problems — system
      architecture, power conversion and distribution, design reviews,
      integration risk, maritime autonomy, subsea sensing, and battery-powered
      systems designed for precision, reliability, and harsh environments.
    </p>

    <p>
      I hold an M.S. in Electrical Engineering from Johns Hopkins with a focus
      in power electronics and analog circuit design, and I maintain an active
      Top Secret clearance.
    </p>
  </div>

  <ul class="mt-8 flex flex-wrap gap-2" aria-label="Core competencies">
    {competencies.map((c) => <li><Tag label={c} /></li>)}
  </ul>
</section>
